  <header class="post-header">
    <h2 class="post-title">Language, Information, and Learning at Yale (LILY)</h2>
  </header>


  <div class = "row">
    <div class = "left">
      <p align="left"> This is the website for the LILY (Language, Information, and Learning at Yale) Lab at the Department of Computer Science at Yale University. The LILY Lab started in Spring 2017 with Professor <a href="http://www.cs.yale.edu/homes/radev/"> Dragomir Radev </a> joining Yale University. Our interests include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li> Natural Language Processing </li>
        <ul>
            <li> Information Retrieval </li>
            <li> Text Summarization </li>
            <li> Syntactic Parsing </li>
        </ul>
        <li> Machine Learning </li> 
        <ul>
            <li> Neural Networks </li>
        </ul>
    </ul>
</div>
</div>
